a = d/\sqrt 2
A
 y^2 = x^2 + \frac 14d^2 
 d^2 = 4(y^2 - x^2) \iff d = 2\sqrt{y^2 - x^2}. 
 a = \frac d{\sqrt 2} = \sqrt 2 \cdot \sqrt{y^2 - x^2} 
 A = a^2 = 2 \cdot (y^2 - x^2) 
 V = \frac 13 A \cdot x = \frac 23 \cdot (y^2 - x^2). 
